The play command, p, is Edway's equivalent to the line editor's print
command, since audio data are not printed, they are played.  Type a
block address, or a range of addresses, the letter p, and press enter.
Play may be interrupted by pressing any key.  The block where play
stops then becomes the current block.  To play the entire audio, you may
type "1,$p", or ",p" or simply "," without the quotes.  Typing a block
address and pressing enter moves to the selected block and plays it.
Pressing enter alone moves ahead and plays the next block.  Pressing p
alone, or a period, replays the current block.

